title: Kayem Foods Recalls Sausage Products Due To Possible Foreign Matter Contamination
summary: WASHINGTON, April 20, 2015 Kayem Foods, a Chelsea, Mass., establishment, is recalling approximately 59,203 pounds of fully cooked chicken sausage products that may be contaminated with pieces of plastic, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today.The chicken sausage products...
